Privacy Policy for The Silent Classroom

Effective Date: 03/07/2025
Last Updated: 03/07/2025

1. Introduction
Welcome to The Silent Classroom, a VR serious game designed to help players learn ASL in an interactive environment. Your privacy is important to us, and this policy explains what data we collect, how we use it, and your rights.

2. What Information We Collect (VRC.Privacy.1)
We do not automatically collect or store any personal data from users. However, we may receive voluntary feedback from players who choose to share their experience to help us improve the game.

3. How We Use Collected Information (VRC.Privacy.2)
Any feedback provided will be used for the following purposes:

Enhancing gameplay and user experience.
Fixing bugs and optimizing game performance.
Understanding player suggestions for future updates.
We do not use collected information for advertising, tracking, or selling to third parties.

4. How Data is Stored and Shared (VRC.Privacy.3)
No Automatic Data Collection: The game does not collect personal, gameplay, or biometric data.
No Storage of Personal Data: We do not store any in-game actions or interactions.
No Third-Party Sharing: Feedback submitted remains private and is not shared with external entities.

5. User Controls and Data Deletion (VRC.Privacy.4)
Since we do not collect data from players, there is no stored personal data to delete.
If you have provided feedback and want it removed, you may request deletion by contacting us at pritony034@gmail.com

6. Children's Privacy
The Silent Classroom is an educational tool and does not collect personal data from players, including children under 13.

7. Changes to This Privacy Policy
This Privacy Policy may be updated in the future. Any changes will be reflected with a new "Last Updated" date.

8. Contact Information
For any questions or concerns regarding this Privacy Policy, please contact:


Pritony034@gmail.com


